{small|(''2''\u2013''3'')}}\n}}\n|otherlabel4    = Music by\n|otherdata4     = {{Plainlist|\n* [[David Nessim Lawrence|David Lawrence]]\n* Andrew Lippa\n* Adam Schlesinger\n* [[Adam Anders]]\n* Peer Astrom\n* Marco Marinangeli\n* Josh Edmondson\n* Sam Hollander\n* Charity Daw\n* Grant Michaels\n* [[Rock Mafia]]\n* [[Antonina Armato]]\n* [[Tim James (musician)|Tim James]]\n* Andy Dodd\n* Mitch Allan\n}}\n|otherlabel5    = Cinematography\n|otherdata5     = {{Plainlist|\n* Thomas Burstyn {{small|(''1'')}}\n* Mark Iwin {{small|(''2'')}}\n}}\n|otherlabel6    = Edited by\n|otherdata6     = [[Don Brochu]]\n|website        =\n|footnotes      = <!--Use {{note}}s or {{note label}}s to go with {{ref}}s and {{ref label}}s in data parameters.-->\n|sp             =\n}}\n\nThe '''''Descendants'' franchise''' consists of three [[Disney Channel]] [[musical film|musical]] [[fantasy]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2019/07/23/descendants-3-review-disney-dove-sofia-carson-cameron-dove-booboo-stewart/|title=Review: 'Descendants 3' Is Both A Satisfying Finale And The End Of An Era|last=Mendelson|first=Scott|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-08-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/cameron-boyce-dies-disney-jessie-descendants-star-age-20/|title=Cameron Boyce, Star of Disney's 'Descendants,' Dies at 20|date=2019-07-07|website=TheWrap|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-06}}</ref> [[Adventure film|adventure]]-[[comedy]] films directed by [[Kenny Ortega]] and created by [[Josann McGibbon]] and Sara Parriott. It is a [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of the [[Disney Princess]] franchise and serves as a continuation after the [[List of Walt Disney Animation Studios films|Disney Animated Classics series]]. Starring [[Dove Cameron]], [[Cameron Boyce]], [[Sofia Carson]] and [[Booboo Stewart]]<!--- do not add China Anne McClain as she did not appear in the first film nor the animated spinoff ---> each film chronicles the lives of the teenage children of four Disney-villains on the Isle of the Lost, and their move to Auradon at the request of the teenage son of [[Belle (Disney)|Queen Belle]] and [[Beast (Beauty and the Beast)|King Beast]]. The [[Descendants (2015 film)|first film]] was released as a [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] in July 2015\u2014however, following its success, a [[Descendants 2|sequel]] was put into production and premiered across six Disney-owned networks in 2017. In 2019, the [[Descendants 3|third film]] premiered on Disney Channel. Each film was accompanied by original music, and film soundtrack; the [[Descendants (soundtrack)|first soundtrack]] peaked at number one in the US, while the [[Descendants 2 (soundtrack)|second soundtrack]] peaked at number six.\n\n==Film series==\n===''Descendants'' (2015)===\n{{main|Descendants (2015 film)}}\n\n''Descendants'' premiered on July 31, 2015 on [[Disney Channel]], and received immediate commercial success. Prior to its premiere, it was viewed more than one million times on the Disney Now app.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2015/07/30/disneys-descendants-garners-over-one-million-views-on-the-watch-disney-channel-app-ahead-of-its-television-premiere-tomorrow-689400/20150730disney01/|title=Disney's \"Descendants\" Garners Over One Million Views on the WATCH Disney Channel App Ahead of Its Television Premiere Tomorrow|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=July 30, 2015|accessdate=July 31, 2015}}</ref> On its premiere night, the film received 6.6 million viewers, becoming the most-watched broadcast on the network of 2015, and the highest-rated broadcast on the network since 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/ratings/descendants-ratings-disney-channel-1201554266/|title= Disney Channel's ''Descendants'' Bewitches 6.6 Million in Friday Premiere|work=Variety|last=Kessell|first=Rick|date=August 1, 2015|accessdate=August 1, 2015}}</ref> The film later went onto become the fifth most-watched original movie on cable television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.multichannel.com/news/content/descendants-now-fifth-most-watched-cable-movie/393054|title='Descendants' Now Fifth Most Watched Cable Movie|work=Multichannel|accessdate=August 23, 2015}}</ref> The film's soundtrack debuted atop of the US ''[[Billboard 200]]'', becoming the first [[List of Disney Channel movies|Disney Channel original movie]] to do so since ''[[High School Musical 2]]'' achieved the same feat in 2007.\n\nIn the United States of Auradon, [[Belle (Disney)|Belle]] and [[Beast (Disney)|Beast]] rule as king and queen, twenty years after they married, united the settings of many [[List of Disney theatrical animated features|Disney animated films]], and banished all villains to the Isle of the Lost, a [[slum]] surrounded by a magic-suppressing barrier. Beast plans to abdicate in favor of his and Belle's son, Ben, who announces a program to invite four children from the Isle of the Lost to live in Auradon, away from the influence of their villainous parents: Carlos, son of [[Cruella de Vil]]; Jay, son of [[Jafar (Disney character)|Jafar]]; Evie, daughter of [[Evil Queen (Disney)|the Evil Queen]]; and their gang's leader Mal, daughter of [[Maleficent]]. Maleficent orders them to steal the [[List of Disney's Cinderella characters#The Fairy Godmother|Fairy Godmother]]'s [[magic wand]] and deactivate the barrier, so Maleficent can conquer Auradon.  But the four find themselves fitting in and enjoying a normal childhood, and Mal begins a relationship with Ben, supplanting Audrey, daughter of [[Aurora (Disney character)|Princess Aurora]] and Prince Phillip.  When the barrier is inadvertently dispelled, Maleficent attacks Ben's coronation and transforms into a [[dragon]].  With Ben encouraging her to make her own choice, Mal decides to be good. She and her friends rebuke Maleficent, turning her into a small [[lizard]], from which state she can recover if she fills her heart with love. The people of Auradon celebrate.\n\n===''Descendants 2'' (2017)===\n{{main|Descendants 2}}\n''Descendants 2'' was announced on August 15, 2015, at the D23 Expo.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/s/descendants-sequel-ordered-disney-channel-200158025.html|title=Descendants Sequel Ordered at Disney Channel|website=www.yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-06}}</ref> The film premiered on July 21, 2017, and was simulcast on six channels: [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]], [[Disney Channel]], [[Disney XD]], [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]], [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]], and [[Lifetime Movies]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/scene/vpage/descendants-2-premiere-dove-cameron-disney-channel-1202493764/|title=\u2018Descendants 2\u2019 Cast Talks \u2018Bigger\u2019 Sets and Musical Numbers at Disney Channel Premiere|last=Saval|first=Malina|last2=Saval|first2=Malina|date=2017-07-12|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-08-06}}</ref> The movie was watched by 5.3 million viewers on Disney Channel and 8.9 million through all six networks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/more-tv-news/descendants-2-is-bigger-but-also-smaller-than-its-predecessor/|title=\u2018Descendants 2\u2019 is bigger (but also smaller) than its predecessor [Updated]|last=Porter|first=Rick|date=2017-07-24|website=TV By The Numbers|language=en|access-date=2019-08-06}}</ref>\n\nMal struggles with her new celebrity life as King Ben's girlfriend, secretly using magic to maintain a lifestyle she feels is a fa\u00e7ade.  Mal decides she does not belong in Auradon; she returns to the Isle, where gang leadership has fallen to her old rival, pirate captain Uma ([[Ursula (The Little Mermaid)|Ursula]]'s daughter), and her first and second mates, respectively, Harry ([[Captain Hook]]'s son) and Gil ([[Gaston (Beauty and the Beast)|Gaston]]'s son). Evie, Jay, and Carlos agree to help Ben find her, but Mal rejects Ben, believing it best for him and Auradon. Uma captures Ben and demands the Fairy Godmother's wand in exchange for his life. Uma resents not being chosen to live in Auradon; Ben respects her as a leader and invites her to Auradon, but she vows to make her own way there instead. Using a [[3D printing|3D-printed]] decoy wand, Mal's group rescues Ben. At the shipboard Royal Cotillion, Uma appears as Ben's date and he announces he will destroy the barrier; Mal realizes Uma has cast a spell on Ben. When Mal discovers Ben commissioned a portrait that depicts her as she was before she changed herself with magic, she accepts the emotion of love and kisses Ben, breaking the spell. Uma and Mal battle, transforming into an [[octopus]] and a [[dragon]], respectively. Ben tries to negotiate with Uma, but she leaves, unreconciled. Evie asks to bring more children from the Isle to Auradon and Ben agrees.\n\n===''Descendants 3'' (2019)===\n{{main|Descendants 3}}\n\nDisney Channel ordered the third film of the franchise on February 16, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/disney-announces-descendants-3-1202703195/|title=Disney Announces 'Descendants 3' for 2019|work=Variety|author=Ariana Brockington|date=February 16, 2018|accessdate=2018-02-17}}</ref> The film premiered on August 2, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1036123/hades-is-pretty-mad-in-first-look-at-cheyenne-jackson-s-new-descendants-3-villain|title=Hades Is Pretty Mad in First Look at Cheyenne Jackson's New Descendants 3 Villain|website=EOnline.com|author=Lauren Piester|date=April 27, 2019|accessdate=April 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Descendants 3 Gets August Premiere Date, New Music Video \u2014 Watch|url=https://tvline.com/2019/05/31/descendants-3-premiere-date-watch-good-to-be-bad-music-video/|work=[[TVLine]]|date=May 31, 2019}}</ref> The movie received 4.6 million viewers on its premiere night.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-8-2-2019.html|title=UPDATED: SHOWBUZZDAILY\u2019s Top 150 Friday Cable Originals\u00a0& Network Finals: 8.2.2019 {{!}} Showbuzz Daily|website=www.showbuzzdaily.com|access-date=2019-08-06}}</ref>\n\nIn the film, Ben proposes to Mal, making her the future queen of Auradon. However, threats from Uma, Mal's father Hades and Ben's ex-girlfriend Audrey has Mal trying to stop evil once and for all. While Mal, Evie, Jay and Carlos are recruiting a new generation of villain kids, Hades is trying to breach through the barrier, then Audrey steals the crown and the scepter and becomes the evil version of herself. The VKs return to the Isle of the Lost on a mission to retrieve Hades' ember and later, Uma, Harry and Gil teams up with Mal and the others to stop Audrey from destroying Auradon.\n\n==Cast members==\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:100%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20%;\"| Characters\n! colspan=\"3\" | Films\n|-\n! style=\"width:20%;\"| ''[[Descendants (2015 film)|Descendants]]''\n! style=\"width:20%;\"| ''[[Descendants 2]]''\n! style=\"width:20%;\"| ''[[Descendants 3]]''\n|-\n! Mal\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[Dove Cameron]]\n|-\n! Carlos\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[Cameron Boyce]]\n|-\n! Evie\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[Sofia Carson]]\n|-\n! Jay\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[Booboo Stewart]]\n|-\n! Ben\n| colspan=\"3\" | Mitchell Hope\n|-\n![[Fairy Godmother (Disney)|Fairy Godmother]]\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[Melanie Paxson]]\n|-\n! Jane\n| colspan=\"3\" | Brenna D'Amico\n|-\n! Doug\n| colspan=\"3\" | Zachary Gibson\n|-\n! Chad\n| colspan=\"3\" | Jedidiah Goodacre\n|-\n! [[Belle (Disney)|Belle]]\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[Keegan Connor Tracy]]\n|-\n! [[Beast (Disney)|Beast]]\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[Dan Payne]]\n|-\n! Lonnie\n| colspan=\"2\" | [[Dianne Doan]]\n| colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\"|\n|-\n! Audrey\n| colspan=\"1\" | [[Sarah Jeffery]]\n| colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightgrey;\"|\n| colspan=\"1\" | Sarah Jeffery\n|-\n! [[Cruella de Vil]]\n| colspan=\"1\" | [[Wendy Raquel Robinson]]\