{"title_page": "Christiane Bonnelle", "text_new": "{{short description|French physicist}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name        = Christiane Bonnelle\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| image       =         <!--(filename only, i.e. without \"File:\" prefix)-->\n| image_size  = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_date  =         <!--{{birth date |YYYY|MM|DD}}-->\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = {{death date|2016|08|21}}\n| other_names = \n| residence   = \n| citizenship = \n| nationality = French\n| fields      = [[Spectroscopy|Spectral analysis]]\n[[Spectroheliograph|Spectroheliograms]] of the [[solar corona]]\n[[X-ray spectroscopy]]\n| workplaces  = [[Centre national de la recherche scientifique|CNRS]] <br/>\n[[Sorbonne]]\nLaboratory of Physical Chemistry, [[Pierre and Marie Curie University]]\n| patrons     = \n| alma_mater  = [[Sorbonne]] ([[Bachelor of Science]], 1954; [[Doctor of Science]], 1964)\n| thesis_title =        <!--(or  | thesis1_title =  and  | thesis2_title = )-->\n| thesis_url  =         <!--(or  | thesis1_url  =   and  | thesis2_url  =  )-->\n| thesis_year =         <!--(or  | thesis1_year =   and  | thesis2_year =  )-->\n| doctoral_advisor =    <!--(or  | doctoral_advisors = )-->\n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students = \n| known_for   = \n| influences  =[[Yvette Cauchois]] \n| influenced  = \n| awards      = [[CNRS Bronze Medal]]\nChevalier (Knight) of the ''[[Ordre des Palmes Acad\u00e9miques]]''\n| signature   =         <!--(filename only)-->\n| signature_alt = \n| website     =         <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}-->\n| footnotes   = \n| honorific_prefix = Professor\n| honorific_suffix =\n| education   = \n}}\n\n'''Christiane Bonnelle''' ({{IPA-fr|k\u0281istjan b\u0254n\u025bl|-|Fr-Christiane Bonnelle.ogg}}, died 21 August 2016) was a [[French people|French]] physicist and pioneering [[Spectroscopy|spectroscopist]], who served as professor [[emeritus]] at [[Pierre and Marie Curie University]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.upmc.fr/fr/espace_des_personnels/disparitions/disparition_christiane_bonnelle.html |title=Disparition de Christiane Bonnelle |website=Universit\u00e9 Pierre et Marie Curie}}</ref>\n\n==Career and Education==\n\nBonnelle studied at the [[Sorbonne]], from which she received [[Bachelor of science]] and [[Doctor of science]] degrees.<ref name=\"CWP\">{{cite web|last1=Byers|first1=N|last2=Hamermesh|first2=Bernard|title=Bonnelle, Christiane|url=http://cwp.library.ucla.edu/Phase2/Bonnelle,_Christiane@871234567.html|website=CWP|publisher=University of California|accessdate=13 August 2016}}</ref> After completing her degree, Bonnelle worked at [[Centre national de la recherche scientifique|CNRS]] in 1955 where she worked as an intern and then researcher. In 1960 she started working as an assistant professor at the [[Paris-Sorbonne University|Sorbonne]], becoming a professor in 1967. She moved to Pierre and Marie Curie University in 1974, where she became director of the Laboratory of Physical Chemistry in 1979. Bonnelle worked in this role until 1990.\n\n==Research==\n\nBonnelle's research on [[Surface science|solid-solid interfaces]] produced developments in the measurement of the [[nanometre]], which facilitated developments in [[Electron microprobe|electron probes]] produced by [[CAMECA]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Bonnelle|first1=Christiane|last2=Blaise|first2=Guy|last3=Le Gressus|first3=Claude|last4=Tr\u00e9heux|first4=Daniel|title=Les isolants|date=2010|publisher=Lavoisier|isbn=9782743017927|page=ix|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=RdDuAQAAQBAJ|accessdate=13 August 2016|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\nIn 1967 she received a [[CNRS Gold medal|CNRS bronze medal]]. She is also a chevalier of the ''[[Ordre des Palmes Acad\u00e9miques]]''.\n\n== Selected publications ==\n* \"Distribution des \u00e9tats f dans les m\u00e9taux et les oxyde de terres rares\", ''Journal de Physique'', 32, C4-230 (1971) with R.C. Karnatak (DOI: 10.1051/jphyscol:1971443). This paper described observations of [[excited state]]s.\n* \"Analyses par spectroscopie X des distributions 5f de l'uranium dans le m\u00e9tal et UO\", ''Journal de Physique'', 35 295-299 (1979) with G. Lach\u00e8re (DOI: 10.1051/jphys:01974003503029500). This paper dealt with [[Transition radiation|radiative transitions]] on [[uranium]].<ref name=\"CWP\" />\n* \"Resonant X-ray Emission Spectroscopy in Solids\", ''Advances in X-Ray Spectroscopy: Contributions in Honour of Professor Y. Cauchois'' ([[Elsevier]], 2013).\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bonnelle, Christiane}}\n[[Category:French physical chemists]]\n[[Category:Spectroscopists]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:2016 deaths]]\n[[Category:French women scientists]]\n[[Category:French women chemists]]\n[[Category:French women physicists]]\n[[Category:Chevaliers of the Ordre des Palmes Acad\u00e9miques]]\n[[Category:French physicists]]\n[[Category:20th-century French scientists]]\n<!--[[Category:21st-century French scientists]]-->\n[[Category:20th-century chemists]]\n[[Category:21st-century chemists]]\n[[Category:20th-century physicists]]\n[[Category:21st-century physicists]]\n[[Category:20th-century women scientists]]\n[[Category:21st-century women scientists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French physicist}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name        = Christiane Bonnelle\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| image       =         <!--(filename only, i.e. without \"File:\" prefix)-->\n| image_size  = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_date  =         <!--{{birth date |YYYY|MM|DD}}-->\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = {{death date|2016|08|21}}\n| other_names = \n| residence   = \n| citizenship = \n| nationality = French\n| fields      = [[Spectroscopy|Spectral analysis]]\n[[Spectroheliograph|Spectroheliograms]] of the [[Corona|Solar Corona]]\n[[X-ray spectroscopy]]\n| workplaces  = [[Centre national de la recherche scientifique|CNRS]] <br/>\n[[Sorbonne]]\nLaboratory of Physical Chemistry, [[Pierre and Marie Curie University]]\n| patrons     = \n| alma_mater  = [[Sorbonne]] ([[Bachelor of Science]], 1954; [[Doctor of Science]], 1964)\n| thesis_title =        <!--(or  | thesis1_title =  and  | thesis2_title = )-->\n| thesis_url  =         <!--(or  | thesis1_url  =   and  | thesis2_url  =  )-->\n| thesis_year =         <!--(or  | thesis1_year =   and  | thesis2_year =  )-->\n| doctoral_advisor =    <!--(or  | doctoral_advisors = )-->\n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students = \n| known_for   = \n| influences  =[[Yvette Cauchois]] \n| influenced  = \n| awards      = [[CNRS Bronze Medal]]\nChevalier (Knight) of the ''[[Ordre des Palmes Acad\u00e9miques]]''\n| signature   =         <!--(filename only)-->\n| signature_alt = \n| website     =         <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}-->\n| footnotes   = \n| honorific_prefix = Professor\n| honorific_suffix =\n| education   = \n}}\n\n'''Christiane Bonnelle''' ({{IPA-fr|k\u0281istjan b\u0254n\u025bl|-|Fr-Christiane Bonnelle.ogg}}, died 21 August 2016) was a [[French people|French]] physicist and pioneering [[Spectroscopy|spectroscopist]], who served as professor [[emeritus]] at [[Pierre and Marie Curie University]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.upmc.fr/fr/espace_des_personnels/disparitions/disparition_christiane_bonnelle.html |title=Disparition de Christiane Bonnelle |website=Universit\u00e9 Pierre et Marie Curie}}</ref>\n\n==Career and Education==\n\nBonnelle studied at the [[Sorbonne]], from which she received [[Bachelor of science]] and [[Doctor of science]] degrees.<ref name=\"CWP\">{{cite web|last1=Byers|first1=N|last2=Hamermesh|first2=Bernard|title=Bonnelle, Christiane|url=http://cwp.library.ucla.edu/Phase2/Bonnelle,_Christiane@871234567.html|website=CWP|publisher=University of California|accessdate=13 August 2016}}</ref> After completing her degree, Bonnelle worked at [[Centre national de la recherche scientifique|CNRS]] in 1955 where she worked as an intern and then researcher. In 1960 she started working as an assistant professor at the [[Paris-Sorbonne University|Sorbonne]], becoming a professor in 1967. She moved to Pierre and Marie Curie University in 1974, where she became director of the Laboratory of Physical Chemistry in 1979. Bonnelle worked in this role until 1990.\n\n==Research==\n\nBonnelle's research on [[Surface science|solid-solid interfaces]] produced developments in the measurement of the [[nanometre]], which facilitated developments in [[Electron microprobe|electron probes]] produced by [[CAMECA]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Bonnelle|first1=Christiane|last2=Blaise|first2=Guy|last3=Le Gressus|first3=Claude|last4=Tr\u00e9heux|first4=Daniel|title=Les isolants|date=2010|publisher=Lavoisier|isbn=9782743017927|page=ix|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=RdDuAQAAQBAJ|accessdate=13 August 2016|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\nIn 1967 she received a [[CNRS Gold medal|CNRS bronze medal]]. She is also a chevalier of the ''[[Ordre des Palmes Acad\u00e9miques]]''.\n\n== Selected publications ==\n* \"Distribution des \u00e9tats f dans les m\u00e9taux et les oxyde de terres rares\", ''Journal de Physique'', 32, C4-230 (1971) with R.C. Karnatak (DOI: 10.1051/jphyscol:1971443). This paper described observations of [[excited state]]s.\n* \"Analyses par spectroscopie X des distributions 5f de l'uranium dans le m\u00e9tal et UO\", ''Journal de Physique'', 35 295-299 (1979) with G. Lach\u00e8re (DOI: 10.1051/jphys:01974003503029500). This paper dealt with [[Transition radiation|radiative transitions]] on [[uranium]].<ref name=\"CWP\" />\n* \"Resonant X-ray Emission Spectroscopy in Solids\", ''Advances in X-Ray Spectroscopy: Contributions in Honour of Professor Y. Cauchois'' ([[Elsevier]], 2013).\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bonnelle, Christiane}}\n[[Category:French physical chemists]]\n[[Category:Spectroscopists]]\n[[Category:Year o